## Tokens — single source of truth

| Token | File |
|---|---|
| Colors | `Assets.xcassets` (Color Sets, Any + Dark variants) referenced via `Theme.Color.*` |
| Spacing | `<App>/Theme/Tokens.swift` `Theme.Spacing` |
| Type | `<App>/Theme/Tokens.swift` `Theme.Font` |
| Radius | `<App>/Theme/Tokens.swift` `Theme.Radius` |
| Shadow | `<App>/Theme/Tokens.swift` `Theme.Shadow` |
| Motion | `<App>/Theme/Tokens.swift` `Theme.Motion` |
| Theme injection | `<App>/Theme/ThemeModifier.swift` (apply once at app root via `.withTheme()`) |

**NEVER use values outside these tokens.** No `.padding(13)`, no `Color(hex: "#3a4f6b")`, no `.cornerRadius(7)`, no `.system(size: 14)` outside `Theme.Font`.

## Press feedback (project-wide choice)

Pick one and stick with it: **{{PRESS_FEEDBACK}}**  (scale | opacity)

Implemented in a single custom `ButtonStyle` under `<App>/Theme/Buttons/`.

## Density mode

**{{DENSITY_MODE}}**  (airy | balanced | dense)

Touch targets remain ≥ 44pt regardless of density.

## Dark mode

**{{DARK_MODE}}**  (required | optional | none)

If `required`: every `Color("...")` asset must have both `Any Appearance` and `Dark Appearance` variants. Verified at every UI Audit (U9).

## iPad support

**{{IPAD_SUPPORT}}**  (yes | no)

If `yes`: use `NavigationSplitView` for top-level navigation, `Form` size classes for adaptive layout, and respect both regular and compact size classes.

## Icon library

**SF Symbols only.** Never Lucide / Phosphor / FontAwesome / Material Icons / custom SVG sprite system for system iconography. Custom `Image("...")` only for brand artwork.

## Custom typography

**{{CUSTOM_TYPOGRAPHY}}**  (none | <font name>)

If a custom font is declared, it MUST be wrapped in `Theme.Font` with a `.system(...)` fallback so Dynamic Type still works.

## Verification command

Before claiming any UI work done, run:

```bash
swiftlint --strict
```

This catches magic numbers, banned gradients, filler copy, hex literals, and buzzwords. The command must exit 0.

